Network and internet security consists of:
	Measures to deter, prevent, detect, and correct security violations that involve transmission of information. 


Computer Security objectives:
	Confidentiality:
		Data confidentiality - Assure that private information not made available to any unauthorized users
		Privacy - Assures individuals control or influence over information that may be collected and stored, and to whom that information is disclosed 

	Integrity:
		Data integrity - Assures that information and programs are changed only in a specified and authorized manner
		System integrity - Assures that a system performs its intended function in an unimpaired manner, free from unauthorized manipulation 

	Availability:
		Systems work promptly and service is not denied to authorized users. 



